{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.77",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 77,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 77 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:1",
      "text": "Understanding for Asaph. Attend, O my people, to my law: incline your ears to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:2",
      "text": "I will open my mouth in parables: I will utter propositions from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:3",
      "text": "How great things have we heard and known, and our fathers have told us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:4",
      "text": "They have not been hidden from their children, in another generation. Declaring the praises of the Lord, and his powers, and his wonders which he hath done.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:5",
      "text": "And he set up a testimony in Jacob: and made a law in Israel. How great things he commanded our fathers, that they should make the same known to their children:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:6",
      "text": "That another generation might know them. The children that should be born and should rise up, and declare them to their children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:7",
      "text": "That they may put their hope in God and may not forget the works of God: and may seek his commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:8",
      "text": "That they may not become like their fathers, a perverse and exasperating generation. A generation that set not their heart aright: and whose spirit was not faithful to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:9",
      "text": "The sons of Ephraim who bend and shoot with the bow: they have turned back in the day of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:10",
      "text": "They kept not the covenant of God: and in his law they would not walk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:11",
      "text": "And they forgot his benefits, and his wonders that he had shewn them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:12",
      "text": "Wonderful things did he do in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Tanis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:13",
      "text": "He divided the sea and brought them through: and he made the waters to stand as in a vessel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:14",
      "text": "And he conducted them with a cloud by day: and all the night with a light of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:15",
      "text": "He struck the rock in the wilderness: and gave them to drink, as out of the great deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:16",
      "text": "He brought forth water out of the rock: and made streams run down as rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:17",
      "text": "And they added yet more sin against him: they provoked the most High to wrath in the place without water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:18",
      "text": "And they tempted God in their hearts, by asking meat for their desires.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:19",
      "text": "And they spoke ill of God: they said: Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:20",
      "text": "Because he struck the rock, and the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed. Can he also give bread, or provide a table for his people?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:21",
      "text": "Therefore the Lord heard, and was angry: and a fire was kindled against Jacob, and wrath came up against Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:22",
      "text": "Because they believed not in God: and trusted not in his salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:23",
      "text": "And he had commanded the clouds from above, and had opened the doors of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:24",
      "text": "And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them the bread of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:25",
      "text": "Man ate the bread of angels: he sent them provisions in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:26",
      "text": "He removed the south wind from heaven: and by his power brought in the southwest wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:27",
      "text": "And he rained upon them flesh as dust: and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:28",
      "text": "And they fell in the midst of their camp, round about their pavilions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:29",
      "text": "So they did eat, and were filled exceedingly, and he gave them their desire:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:30",
      "text": "they were not defrauded of that which they craved. As yet their meat was in their mouth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:31",
      "text": "And the wrath of God came upon them. And he slew the fat ones amongst them, and brought down the chosen men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:32",
      "text": "In all these things they sinned still: and they behaved not for his wondrous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:33",
      "text": "And their days were consumed in vanity, and their years in haste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:34",
      "text": "When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned, and came to him early in the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:35",
      "text": "And they remembered that God was their helper: and the most high God their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:36",
      "text": "And they loved him with their mouth: and with their tongue they lied unto him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:37",
      "text": "But their heart was not right with him: nor were they counted faithful in his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:38",
      "text": "But he is merciful, and will forgive their sins: and will not destroy them. And many a time did he turn away his anger: and did not kindle all his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:39",
      "text": "And he remembered that they are flesh: a wind that goeth and returneth not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:40",
      "text": "How often did they provoke him in the desert: and move him to wrath in the place without water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:41",
      "text": "And they turned back and tempted God: and grieved the holy one of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:42",
      "text": "They remembered not his hand, in the day that he redeemed them from the hand of him that afflicted them:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:43",
      "text": "How he wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Tanis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:44",
      "text": "And he turned their rivers into blood, and their showers that they might not drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:45",
      "text": "He sent amongst them divers sorts of flies, which devoured them: and frogs which destroyed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.46",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:46",
      "text": "And he gave up their fruits to the blast, and their labours to the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.47",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:47",
      "text": "And he destroyed their vineyards with hail, and their mulberry trees with hoarfrost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.48",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:48",
      "text": "And he gave up their cattle to the hail, and their stock to the fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.49",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:49",
      "text": "And he sent upon them the wrath of his indignation: indignation and wrath and trouble, which he sent by evil angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.50",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:50",
      "text": "He made a way for a path to his anger: he spared not their souls from death, and their cattle he shut up in death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.51",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:51",
      "text": "And he killed all the firstborn in the land of Egypt: the firstfruits of all their labour in the tabernacles of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.52",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:52",
      "text": "And he took away his own people as sheep: and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.53",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:53",
      "text": "And he brought them out in hope and they feared not: and the sea overwhelmed their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.54",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:54",
      "text": "And he brought them into the mountain of his sanctuary: the mountain which his right hand had purchased. And he cast out the Gentiles before them: and by lot divided to them their land by a line of distribution.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.55",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:55",
      "text": "And he made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tabernacles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.56",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:56",
      "text": "Yet they tempted, and provoked the most high God: and they kept not his testimonies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.57",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:57",
      "text": "And they turned away, and kept not the covenant: even like their fathers they were turned aside as a crooked bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.58",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:58",
      "text": "They provoked him to anger on their hills: and moved him to jealousy with their graven things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.59",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:59",
      "text": "God heard, and despised them, and he reduced Israel exceedingly as it were to nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.60",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:60",
      "text": "And he put away the tabernacle of Silo, his tabernacle where he dwelt among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.61",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:61",
      "text": "And he delivered their strength into captivity: and their beauty into the hands of the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.62",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:62",
      "text": "And he shut up his people under the sword: and he despised his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.63",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:63",
      "text": "Fire consumed their young men: and their maidens were not lamented.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.64",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword: and their widows did not mourn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.65",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:65",
      "text": "And the Lord was awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that hath been surfeited with wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.66",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:66",
      "text": "And he smote his enemies on the hinder parts: he put them to an everlasting reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.67",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:67",
      "text": "And he rejected the tabernacle of Joseph: and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.68",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 68,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:68",
      "text": "But he chose the tribe of Juda, mount Sion which he loved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.77.69",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 69,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:69",
